translated: Cagnell, Sven Clements, first naval engineer, Karlskrona, now Stockholm, b. January 5, 1914 in Uddevalla. Married in 1940 to Gerd Lindwall, with children: Lennart b. 1941, Hans b. 1943. He graduated from Norra Real High School in Stockholm in 1932 and KTH as a civil engineer in 1936. He received naval training in 1936, was employed at Götaverken in 1937, and at Swan, Hunter & Wigham Richardsons shipyard in Newcastle-on-Tyne in 1938, where he became a marine engineer. The same year, he performed protective duties at the Gotland airfield and went on a long trip to South America. In 1938-1939, he went on summer trips to France and England. He became a naval marine in 1940 and a divisional engineer on a destroyer in 1941. He worked on support ships at Golland from 1941-1943 and was in charge of marine engineering at Filottanas and off the coast of Karlskrona from 1943-1945. He was the head of naval engineering at the naval base in Karlskrona from 1945-1947 and became the first naval engineer in 1947. He served in the naval reserve from 1947.
